Drvperf is an utility to measure various characteristics of mass storage
devices and mass storage subsystem as a whole in Linux environment.
See manual page: $ man -l drvperf.1

Build:
  $ mkdir build
  $ cd build
  $ cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release ..
  $ make

Changelog:
  (1.7) Added --max-buffer-size option
  (1.7) Allow fractionals in option values
  (1.7) Added --rndseed option

